<div id="descriptionContainer">
  
      <div id="description" class="readable stacked" style="right:0">
        
<span id="freeTextContainer13694206981021539395">Originally appearing as a series of articles in <i>The New Yorker</i>, Hannah Arendt’s authoritative and stunning report on the trial of Nazi leader Adolf Eichmann sparked a flurry of debate upon its publication. <br/><br/>This revised edition includes material that came to light after the trial, as well as Arendt’s postscript directly addressing the controversy that arose over her account</span>
  <span id="freeText13694206981021539395" style="display:none">Originally appearing as a series of articles in <i>The New Yorker</i>, Hannah Arendt’s authoritative and stunning report on the trial of Nazi leader Adolf Eichmann sparked a flurry of debate upon its publication. <br /><br />This revised edition includes material that came to light after the trial, as well as Arendt’s postscript directly addressing the controversy that arose over her account. A major journalistic triumph by an intellectual of singular influence, <br /><br /><i>Eichmann in Jerusalem</i> is as shocking as it is informative—an unflinching look at one of the most unsettling and unsettled issues of the twentieth century that remains hotly debated to this day.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13694206981021539395" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

      </div>
